&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Copper River Technologies&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Construction Engineering Technician&lt;/strong&gt; to support quality assurance, safety management, and technical coordination on complex construction projects administered by the Naval Facilities Engineering Systems Command (NAVFAC) and the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE) at JEBLC, Virginia. This role requires hands-on oversight at active construction sites to ensure compliance with contract requirements, safety regulations, and quality standards. The ideal candidate will be detail-oriented, proactive, and adept at collaborating with government clients, contractors, and subcontractors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities (include but are not limited to):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure contractor compliance with approved Quality Control Plans, including participation in the three-phase inspection process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct site inspections, witness system tests, and support commissioning of critical systems (HVAC, electrical, fire/life safety, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify materials for compliance, condition, and approval for payment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage field documentation including daily reports, quality records, and progress photos.&lt;/li&gt;
